                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16901636" author="ajisakaa" created="Wed, 7 Aug 2019 02:31:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeagles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeagles&quot;&gt;jeagles&lt;/a&gt; commented, Hadoop project release checker is available (&lt;a href=&quot;https://checker.apache.org/projs/hadoop.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://checker.apache.org/projs/hadoop.html&lt;/a&gt;) and this page should be checked after each release is made.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16912857" author="ajisakaa" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2019 02:07:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed this to trunk, branch-3.2, branch-3.1, branch-2, branch-2.9, and branch-2.8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16912858" author="hudson" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2019 02:10:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FAILURE: Integrated in Jenkins build Hadoop-trunk-Commit #17165 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Hadoop-trunk-Commit/17165/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Hadoop-trunk-Commit/17165/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-16494&quot; title=&quot;Add SHA-256 or SHA-512 checksum to release artifacts to comply with the release distribution policy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-16494&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-16494&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Add SHA-512 checksum to release artifact to comply with (aajisaka: rev 34dd9ee36674be670013d4fc3d9b8f5b36886812)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(edit) dev-support/bin/create-release&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="16927236" author="rohithsharma" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2019 04:21:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aajisaka&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aajisaka&quot;&gt;aajisaka&lt;/a&gt; I created release artifacts for 3.2.1 and trying to verify sha512. I see below error  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;rohithsharmaks@ip-172-31-38-26:~/branch-3.2.1/target/artifacts$ sha512sum -c CHANGELOG.md.sha512
sha512sum: /build/source/target/artifacts/CHANGELOG.md: No such file or directory
/build/source/target/artifacts/CHANGELOG.md: FAILED open or read
sha512sum: WARNING: 1 listed file could not be read
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When sha512 is created, it is taking entire folder path into account because &lt;b&gt;&quot;${i}&quot;&lt;/b&gt; is entire folder patch. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; for i in ${ARTIFACTS_DIR}/*; do
    ${GPG} --use-agent --armor --output &quot;${i}.asc&quot; --detach-sig &quot;${i}&quot;
    sha512sum --tag &quot;${i}&quot; &amp;gt; &quot;${i}.sha512&quot;
  done
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this expected? or need fix to consider only file name. How was earlier md5 was running?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16927241" author="rohithsharma" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2019 04:25:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just checked previous releases where same as above folder path is in md5 files. Looks it is fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16927260" author="ctubbsii" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2019 05:11:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohithsharma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohithsharma&quot;&gt;rohithsharma&lt;/a&gt; While that isn&apos;t a new thing, it is probably still going to be a source of frustration, since it is very unlikely that whoever is verifying the file is going to be doing so in a path that beings with &lt;tt&gt;/build/source/target&lt;/tt&gt;, and therefore, it might be a good idea to address this in a new issue. Do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16927523" author="rohithsharma" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2019 12:29:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;it might be a good idea to address this in a new issue. Do you think?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am +1 for addressing this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
